This article is a presidential proclamation by Barack Obama declaring October 11, 2011, as General Pulaski Memorial Day. The proclamation honors Brigadier General Casimir Pulaski, a Polish patriot who fought for freedom in Poland and later joined the American Revolutionary War. General Pulaski is recognized as the "Father of the American Cavalry" and played a significant role in the war. The proclamation also acknowledges the contributions of Polish Americans to American culture and history. It encourages Americans to commemorate this day with appropriate programs and activities honoring General Pulaski and all those who defend the freedom of the nation.